Description: An R object class designed for single-cell RNA sequencing data, providing tools for data analysis, visualization, and integration.
A matrix-like container where rows represent features of interest (e.g., genes, transcripts) and columns represent samples, used for storing experimental results.
A table or 2-dimensional array-like structure in R, where each column contains values of one variable and each row contains a set of values from each column.
An R data structure that can hold elements of different types (like numbers, strings, vectors, and other lists), allowing for the storage of complex data sets.
A two-dimensional, homogeneous data structure in R, where all elements are of the same type, arranged in rows and columns.
A matrix in R that is optimized for storing large datasets with many zero entries, conserving memory by only storing non-zero elements.
A basic data structure in R that contains elements of the same type, such as numeric, character, or logical, arranged in a single dimension.
